The NFTs industry has grown exponentially in the past few months and has seen a significant highrise within a few days of this new year. But the growth factor behind it cannot be subjected to the market but the innovative ideas behind creating multipurpose NFTs that are beyond just ownership but ownership of value.

Most especially, the gaming industry has massively contributed an added value to NFTs, players now see their NFTs as something that can work for them, use it as their gaming avatar, and make money with it, amongst other many use cases that have been created over time.

NFTs still have more use cases that are still yet to be explored, but gradually, as need calls for them, there will be more innovative ideas to keep NFTs more valuable and maintain their rarity as a collectible. And as the gaming industry is concerned, we are always working to bring the best to market that will make players’ experiences more fun and create more earning opportunities. That’s why we would like to introduce our new SOGA WELCOME NFT.

**SOGA WELCOME NFT**

**Our NFTs**

Initially, Socialgames has created a space for anyone anywhere to play games of their choice on the platform with a free default Hero, which will give them access to play in our Microverse, Cybercity. Players using the default Hero can win in-game rewards, like gold coins, diamonds, food, can upgrade buildings to a certain level, get energy from the Power Generator and more.

But we wanted to give players extra fun and let them explore their full potential of how they are good at the games and how an NFT could even boost their experience and make them have more tasks to do, more buildings to explore and more in-game rewards earn. That’s why we created **SOGA WELCOME NFT**.

**SOGA WELCOME NFT**

This Welcome NFT can also be called “Borrow NFT”; the idea behind it is to let players use a borrowed Hero NFT by Socialgames to play their games so they can experience the fun of playing with a Hero NFT.

Instead of using the default Hero, players can use their borrowed NFTs to play in different games, which they can get from our NFT Heroes shop for free. Players can use it to gain more experience, enjoy more deathmatches, train new skills, win more coins, and have more chances to finish challenges and be on the leaderboard.

The most impressive part of this new NFT is that all experiences, skills, and rewards earnt using this borrowed NFT are all players’ assets, and they can be transferred from the borrowed NFT to their own Rarity Common Hero NFT after they purchase one. This means that all your progress with this NFT is yours, not the borrowed NFTs.

And this is made possible because all progress is saved for the players, it is locked in SOGA Escrow Smart Contract. This makes the experience, skills, and progress unique to you only, it is not transferable to other players.

All players are welcome to use the new Borrowed NFT for free, as it is made available for everyone as a “Welcome NFT.” And on the long run, if you love the New NFT and decide that you want it, you can buy it at any time in the Shop at the original price and mint it, and if you have some silver stars, you will be able to use it to get a 50% discount on the Hero NFT purchase.

**Note:** The new Hero can only be borrowed from among R1 (Rarity 1\) NFTs only.

And after the purchase, all skills, experience, reward, and progress acquired by your “Borrowed NFT” will be kept by your newly purchased Rarity 1 Hero NFT. With that, you can continue building on that and upgrade your Hero to be more powerful and have more skills.

You might be wondering, does this New NFT have some special attributes and features? Yes, it comes with some extra features you get from them as an R1 (Rarity 1 NFT), which makes it different from the default Hero. Let’s check some of the extras:

- **Upgrade the stats of your own Hero:** with this new NFT, players can now upgrade the stats of their Hero, which cannot be done before with the default hero.
- **Train new skills:** The default Hero cannot train for new skills, except using the default skill, and that won’t bring the best out of players. So with this new NFT, you can train and acquire new skills, but the ranking or upgrade limit is 5 (five) instead of the normal 10 for the Rarity Hero NFT. With ranking, players can make their “Borrowed NFT” more powerful, make more progress in different cities and earn more resources and assets.
- **Enjoy buildings like the Gym, Cyborg Corp & Grinders:** Before introducing our New Welcome NFT, the default Hero could not visit or do anything at places like Grinders, Cyborg Corp and Gym.

But this New Hero NFT gives you the ability to do many things that cannot be done with the default Hero and gives you the power to leverage its use and compete with opponents in the game.

Amongst other key features of this new NFT, these are the main ones. We can’t wait to see all the players having their own “Borrowed NFT” and how they can take full advantage of them.

Players that are new to the game, follow this step-by-step guide to getting your New Welcome NFT:

**STEP 1:** Log in into your account

**STEP 2:** After login, you will be immediately directed to your dashboard, which will look like this:

![][image1]

Upon log in into your account, you will see the New Hero R1 picture, which will display your Borrowed NFT. Click the Welcome Pass, which will lead us to step 3

**STEP 3:** Upon clicking the Welcome Pass to claim your free Borrowed NFT, it will pop-up an alert message like this:

![][image2]

Go through the available information to have more clues, but not necessary if you follow this guide from the beginning. Then you will click the orange button with the text “BORROW MY HERO NFT FOR FREE,” which will then take you to Cyborg Corp, where you will be able to access floor 1 of Heroes Shop.

**STEP 4:** When you get to the Heroes Shop on floor 1, you will first choose a worker who will help you in the process of borrowing. Choose a worker:

![][image3]

After choosing your worker, it will take you to the next step.

**STEP 5:** Here, you choose your desired Hero from R1’s available NFTs. You can only choose between Gretha Monev, Dr. Healy, Haku Sadaji, or Charlie.

**Note:** You must have your wallet connected for buying or borrowing an NFT Hero and also have around 0.003 matic for gas fee Price given by Polygon)

![][image4]

When connecting your wallet, you will see two options:  
“Buy in 2 steps” button  
“New Hero” button  
at the bottom center in the price bar. After selecting your desired Hero, proceed to borrow by clicking the “New Hero” button.

![][image5]

A pop up message will appear to complete the procedure, something like this:

Selecting the “New Hero” Welcome Pass will activate the “Borrow NFT Now” button.

![][image6]

Then, borrow it by clicking the “Borrow NFT Now” button and track your progress using the **ORDER STATUS** section as you mint your New Hero NFT.

**To sum up**

With the above step-by-step guide, we hope every new player can get their borrowed NFT and enjoy a more fun gaming experience with it, and once the NFT suits your choice, you’re urged to purchase it and unlock it to be able to reach Rank 10 as normal Hero NFT does, together with the other advantages.

There will be more use cases coming out in the nearest future, and we’re constantly working on creating the best for you and creating a better game economy where everyone has the potential to earn.

We are creating many new advantages and features in this new industry and we will keep on creating and delireving new ideas to Web3.
